1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:04,125
At first, the approach was calm and smooth

2
00:00:05,208 --> 00:00:07,666
The interrogator found nothing he was looking for

3
00:00:08,125 --> 00:00:11,625
Then he began torturing by beating

4
00:00:12,333 --> 00:00:16,166
All over the body with a hose or a stick

5
00:00:16,416 --> 00:00:18,166
Even if our bodies broke under torture

6
00:00:18,458 --> 00:00:20,958
Because more than one prisoner suffered fractures as a result

7
00:00:23,958 --> 00:00:25,333
He kept beating continuously

8
00:00:25,458 --> 00:00:30,166
As long as the person did not lose consciousness

9
00:00:31,125 --> 00:00:33,666
If he found no result, he tried
the <i>shabeh</i> [suspension] method

10
00:00:34,416 --> 00:00:37,708
He lifted the person using the <i>balingo</i>
[hoist] by his hands

11
00:00:38,541 --> 00:00:39,625
So that his feet did not touch the ground

12
00:00:39,958 --> 00:00:43,041
Which forced the prisoner

13
00:00:43,208 --> 00:00:46,500
To confess to whatever the interrogator wanted

14
00:00:46,875 --> 00:00:49,416
Even if the person had done nothing against them at all

15
00:00:49,750 --> 00:00:52,625
We said there was beating and suspension

16
00:00:53,000 --> 00:00:55,625
As for the women, we heard their screams

17
00:00:55,750 --> 00:00:57,208
Without knowing their method of torture

18
00:00:57,333 --> 00:00:59,000
Without hearing the sounds of beating

19
00:00:59,166 --> 00:01:01,541
Or knowing their style of interrogation with women

20
00:01:01,708 --> 00:01:03,666
But interrogations always took place after midnight

21
00:01:04,291 --> 00:01:06,708
And lasted for around three hours

22
00:01:07,041 --> 00:01:10,250
Torture included everyone without exception

23
00:01:10,458 --> 00:01:13,375
And it was done according to the charges brought against them

24
00:01:13,583 --> 00:01:15,625
And based on confessions

25
00:01:16,541 --> 00:01:19,500
Anyone with serious charges

26
00:01:20,916 --> 00:01:24,458
Was tortured by all means until he spoke

27
00:01:24,625 --> 00:01:27,375
They continued even if it led to death

28
00:01:27,625 --> 00:01:29,666
Once, they tortured a man

29
00:01:30,000 --> 00:01:31,416
Before I was detained

30
00:01:31,833 --> 00:01:33,875
His name was Ammar, from al-Baasi village

31
00:01:34,000 --> 00:01:35,666
They kept torturing him until he died

32
00:01:36,250 --> 00:01:38,083
Without extracting any confession

33
00:01:38,666 --> 00:01:41,208
So I realized they had no problem with a prisoner dying

34
00:01:41,333 --> 00:01:42,375
Depending on his case

35
00:01:42,916 --> 00:01:43,958
No problem
